<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Journalism Subdomains</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }

        h1, h2 {
            color: #c0392b; /* Reddish for news/alert */
        }

        .subdomain {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
            padding-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .subdomain h3 {
            margin-bottom: 5px;
            color: #e74c3c; /* Brighter red */
        }

        .subdomain p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .demand, .colleges, .scholarships {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Journalism Subdomains</h1>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Print Journalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Focuses on writing and reporting for newspapers, magazines, and other print publications. It involves in-depth research, interviewing, and editorial skills.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Broadcast Journalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Involves reporting news for television and radio. It requires strong on-camera or on-air presence, as well as video and audio editing skills.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Digital Journalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Covers news reporting for online platforms, including websites, blogs, and social media. It includes multimedia content creation and SEO skills.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Photojournalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Focuses on capturing news through photography. It requires strong visual storytelling skills and technical proficiency in photography.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Investigative Journalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Involves in-depth, long-term reporting to uncover hidden or suppressed information, often involving complex research and analysis.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Sports Journalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Covers reporting on sports events, athletes, and related news. It requires knowledge of various sports and strong writing or broadcasting skills.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Business Journalism</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Focuses on reporting on business, finance, and economic news. It requires knowledge of financial markets and business principles.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="demand">
            <h2>Demand for Journalists</h2>
            <p>The demand for journalists is driven by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>The need for accurate and reliable news in a digital age.</li>
                <li>The rise of online news platforms and multimedia content.</li>
                <li>The importance of investigative journalism in holding power accountable.</li>
                <li>The growth of specialized journalism, such as data journalism and solutions journalism.</li>
                <li>The increasing demand for content creators in various industries.</li>
                <li>The requirement for skilled communicators in public relations and corporate communications.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="colleges">
            <h2>Colleges for Journalism in India</h2>
            <p>Some prominent institutions offering journalism courses include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Indian Institute of Mass Communication (IIMC), New Delhi</li>
                <li>Asian College of Journalism (ACJ), Chennai</li>
                <li>Symbiosis Institute of Media and Communication (SIMC), Pune</li>
                <li>Jamia Millia Islamia, New Delhi</li>
                <li>Lady Shri Ram College for Women (LSR), New Delhi</li>
                <li>Xavier Institute of Communications (XIC), Mumbai</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="scholarships">
            <h2>Scholarships for Journalism Courses</h2>
            <p>Scholarships and financial aid options may include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Merit-based scholarships from universities and colleges.</li>
                <li>Need-based scholarships for students with financial constraints.</li>
                <li>Government scholarships for higher education in media studies.</li>
                <li>Industry-sponsored scholarships from media organizations and foundations.</li>
                <li>Scholarships from private organizations supporting journalism education.</li>
                <li>Specific scholarships offered by institutions for journalism students.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Always verify scholarship details with the respective institutions or government websites.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>